title: Facebook Says Regulator Data Transfer Ruling Will Kill Its EU Operations
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) is unsure if it can continue to run its social media platforms in the European Union if a new Ireland data protection ruling comes into effect.

title: Facebook tells Irish court that probe threatens its EU operations - newspaper
text: Facebook has told Ireland's High Court it cannot see how its services could operate in the European Union if regulators freeze its data transfer mechanism, the Sunday Business Post reported, citing court documents seen by the paper.
